    <!-- research experiences -->
    <section class="testimonials" id="research_experiences">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="wow bounceInLeft animated" data-wow-delay="0.1s" style="visibility: visible;-webkit-animation-delay: 0.1s; -moz-animation-delay: 0.1s; animation-delay: 0.1s;"> 
				<h2>Research Experiences</h2> 
			</div>	
			<!-- row -->
			<div class="row" style="margin-left:10px">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">					
					<div class="col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9">
						<blockquote style="margin-bottom:5px">
							<h4>
								Combining 3D geometry with deep learning for robust registration and retrieval, 2021.01 - 2021.11
							</h4>
							<p>
								Research leader, National University of Singapore.
								<ul>
								    <li>Bulit a multi-view line detection dataset based on MegaDepth dataset.</li>
								    <li>Proposed a weakly-supervised line detection framework using trifocal tensor based multi-view consistency.</li>
								    <li>Proposed a domain adaptive line detection and description framework using homography warping consistency.</li>
                </ul>
							</p>
						</blockquote>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<!-- ./row -->	
            <br>
            <!-- row -->
            			<!-- row -->
			<div class="row" style="margin-left:10px">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">					
					<div class="col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9">
						<blockquote style="margin-bottom:5px">
							<h4>
								Model order reduction method for simulation of planetary gear set based on Arbitrary Lagrangian Eulerian (ALE) formulation, 2018.10 - 2020.07
							</h4>
							<p>
								Research leader, Tsinghua University.
								<ul>
								    <li>Proposed a novel ALE planetary gear set to reduce the degrees of freedom (DOFs) of the system from 10E7 to 10E4</li>
								    <li>By splitting the planet gear into two ALE gears, each ALE planet gear only contacts with the ring or sun gear, making it feasible to develop ALE planetary gear set.</li>
								    <li>Five times acceleration of simulation time with comparable simulation accuracy was achieved compared with ABAQUS.</li>
                </ul>
							</p>
						</blockquote>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<!-- ./row -->	
            <br>
            <!-- row -->
			<div class="row" style="margin-left:10px">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">					
					<div class="col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9">
						<blockquote style="margin-bottom:5px">
							<h4>
								An efficient multibody dynamic modeling method of three-dimensional (3D) contacts in helical gear-shaft system, 2018.02 - 2018.08
							</h4>
							<p>
								Research leader, Tsinghua University.
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Proposed the ALE helical gear, where low-frequency approximation (LFA) technique and ALE formulation were adopted to reduce the system DOFs from 10E6 to 10E3 ~ 10E4.</li>
                                    <li>Simplified the inertial terms in dynamic equations and adopted a high-efficiency contact algorithm based on hierarchical oriented bounding box tree (OBB-tree).</li>
 																		<li>Three-dimensional Timoshenko beam elements in Lagrangian formation were adopted to discretize the shaft.</li>
 																		<li>The proposed method was implemented using C++ and one order of magnitude acceleration of simulation time was achieved with high accuracy, compared with commercial nonlinear finite element software ABAQUS.</li>
                                </ul>
							</p>
						</blockquote>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<!-- ./row -->	
            <br>
            <!-- row -->
			<div class="row" style="margin-left:10px">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">					
					<div class="col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9">
						<blockquote style="margin-bottom:5px">
							<h4>
								Development of evaluation method for sliding wear by multibody dynamics, 2018.06 - 2019.02
							</h4>
							<p>
								Project leader, Tsinghua University, Partner: Mitsubishi Heavy Industries, Japan.
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Established a general low-frequency approximated model using C++, which was successfully applied in the variable-geometry turbocharger (VGT) in this project to improve the computational efficiency by five times.</li>
                                    <li>Adopted the hierarchical OBB-tree method for rapid contact detection in VGT. </li>
                                </ul>
							</p>
						</blockquote>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<!-- ./row -->	
            <br>
            <!-- row -->
			<div class="row" style="margin-left:10px">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">					
					<div class="col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9">
						<blockquote style="margin-bottom:5px">
							<h4>
								Research on dynamic characteristics of helical gears and bevel gears based on ALE formulation, 2018.01 - 2018.10
							</h4>
							<p>
								Research leader, Tsinghua University.
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Established the FE models of four pairs of helical gears with different helix angles and two pairs of bevel gears using Solidworks and Hypermesh.</li>
                                    <li>Developed the corresponding ALE gears for higher efficiency.</li>
                                    <li>Analyzed the dynamic transmission characteristics with correlation to three dimensional contacts and helix angles, for which an algorithm to compute contact lines was proposed.</li>
                                </ul>
							</p>
						</blockquote>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<!-- ./row -->	
            <br>
		</div>
	</section>
